# mcpscan runs clean on its own source. Two intentional exclusions:
#
# tests/fixtures  — fixtures are deliberately vulnerable (that's the point).
# mcpscan/rules   — rule definitions literally contain the attack patterns they
#                   match (regex strings like "os.system" or injection phrases),
#                   so a pattern scanner always flags its own corpus. This is the
#                   classic self-reference case, not a real finding.
tests/fixtures
mcpscan/rules
